{
  "text": "In relation to risk factors, this research found that being of male sex was significantly related to perforation, and this is in line with the results of previous reports [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . A possible explanation for this is elderly males' culture of reluctance to go to hospital, as found in a report by Sheu et al. [CITATION_4] .",
  "citation_candidates": [
